OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA mostly dry and cloudy morning
OL,6,Fwith some bright or sunny intervals, a
OL,7,Ffew showers possible over Argyll and
OL,8,FBute. Dry for all in the afternoon
OL,9,Fwith longer sunny spells developing,
OL,10,Fespecially in the north.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA dry evening with clear
OL,13,Fspells becoming more prolonged as
OL,14,Fcloud clears. Remaining dry overnight
OL,15,Fwith clear spells, leading to a cold
OL,16,Fnight and a frost.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
